From 5da5b911039c97723483ea0d8b20fd0b754ba988 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 14:54:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/7] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Add support for attaching DSCP
  policy to STA

Introduce functionality to add a DSCP policy to a connected STA via the
hostapd_cli. This includes:

- A new helper function add_dscp_policy_to_sta() that adds or updates
  a DSCP policy in the STA's policy list.
- Memory management for dynamically allocated policy entries.
- Integration with the SET_DSCP_POLICY control command to apply the
  parsed policy to the target STA.

Patch-dependency: None
Tag:DAP

Signed-off-by: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 hostapd/ctrl_iface.c |  6 +++
 src/ap/dscp_policy.c | 96 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/ap/dscp_policy.h |  3 ++
 src/ap/sta_info.c    |  7 ++++
 4 files changed, 112 insertions(+)

Index: b/hostapd/ctrl_iface.c
===================================================================
--- a/hostapd/ctrl_iface.c
+++ b/hostapd/ctrl_iface.c
@@ -805,6 +805,12 @@ static int hostapd_ctrl_iface_set_dscp_p
 	if (build_frame_classifier(&policy) < 0)
 		return -1;
 
+	if (add_dscp_policy_to_sta(sta, &policy) < 0) {
+		wpa_printf(MSG_WARNING, "DSCP: Failed to add policy for STA " MACSTR,
